From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Hadrian configurePackageRules to need .conf files

When using a different bootstrap GHC version (e.g., 9.6.7 to build 9.2.8),
Cabal.configurePackage needs dependency packages to be registered in the
package database before it can resolve version constraints.

The original code only calls needLibrary which ensures .a files exist, but
Cabal.configurePackage uses ghc-pkg to check the package database. This
patch adds logic to also need the .conf files for Stage0 dependencies.

Error without this fix:
  "Encountered missing or private dependencies: ghc-boot-th ==9.2.8"

This happens because template-haskell needs ghc-boot-th == 9.2.8, but
the package database only has the bootstrap's ghc-boot-th (different version)
until the source's ghc-boot-th is built and registered.

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
@@ -42,8 +42,17 @@ configurePackageRules = do
         when (pkg == ghcBignum) $ do
           isGmp <- (== "gmp") <$> interpretInContext ctx getBignumBackend
           when isGmp $
             need [buildP -/- "include/ghc-gmp.h"]
-        needLibrary =<< contextDependencies ctx
+        deps <- contextDependencies ctx
+        needLibrary deps
+        -- For Stage0, also ensure dependency packages are registered in the
+        -- package database before configuring. This is needed when using a
+        -- different bootstrap GHC version, as Cabal.configurePackage checks
+        -- version constraints against the package database.
+        when (stage == Stage0) $ do
+            dbPath <- packageDbPath stage
+            depPkgIds <- mapM (pkgIdentifier . package) deps
+            need [dbPath -/- pkgId <.> "conf" | pkgId <- depPkgIds]
         Cabal.configurePackage ctx

     root -/- "**/autogen/cabal_macros.h" %> \out -> do
